spanGrp.span: I will start the story about masu
kar yf f ma.ne z.nth.k.fe ya.br
thkfksi = start, begin; we two have started the place (female)
the place name there, that we started, yabr
nzen.me menz zb.th fe.fe mo.bo sa.tho.ra
where our ancestor arrived as the first one
menz th menz fr.kak.me.nzo f.th kwan.kwir.w.r.mth
the ancestors came one by one
marasi = see, akwir (no inf) = run, thoraksi = appear, search
they were looking for their way, they came this way
when they were looking for a place
our ancestor came to this place here
ritaksi = cross; swnze = large creek close to mibini
over there in swnze he crossed the creek
ythn (irreg,no inf) = be lying down; mare = fallen tree (usually blocks something or goes across something)
the log is still lying there
sa.tho.ra z.y y.md fo.ba zan.ka.ri.sa a.fa k.fok.fo
he arrived here and heard the bird; afa kfokfo
(He said) "this is a place on the high ground there"
san.tho.ra za.ma.ra yf zw.ra.ko kar yf ma.su
he arrived and saw the place. he gave a name to it, the name masu
ritaksi = cross; yaro = he went away; rro = she went away
then he crossed over this way. he walked away.
yak (irreg.) = walk; n can occur directly before the verb, or even before kwa
"I will try to walk this way"
ya.ka.ko ni.ma n sr.zi.gr.thm ka.be z zm.sa
he walked and he tried to look
ka.be zb.thw z zm.sa a.ne fof fa.rem
but there a man who had come earlier. the one from the farem
their ancestor had settled ther first
thar.thar.fa n.bun ma.ne thwa.ni.ya.km ni.ma wa.zu be.r
yaniyak = come; nbun = if they do something
others that came from the side like the wazu clan there
they have their named places there
for example, one place name is wazu
should be: boba not foba; (not mixing them; says nakre)
on the other side, there is muthrata
on the other side, towards here
a.ne fof nzen.me menz mo.ba zn.bri.ma
brigsi = return; ane fof refers to the place (fisor bthan)
that was where our ancestor returned from
first translated as: "he started to look"
ke.ke ka.be z z.ms zwa# z.bri.mo wa.tik yf.nzo zwn.ra
"a man has settled here already." okay, he only gave the place name
this here is the story place
naf.ne m.sak.si zn za.ne zf r
za.ne zf kar t.na r no tr.kr ka.far f.th re.ra
this is high ground here. when there was a big flood
za.ne faf zn ke nof za.fa.fa
this place was not caught by the water
not this one here, not masu
this is why they would call us masu people
kar yf za.ne zf r ma.su
the name of the place is masu
there was a thick forest here
farsi = fell; fz r 'forest ist feminine'
they cut its down for gardening
ze.na ze.na ke.ke ni.ma r fz b.r
there is no more forest of this type today
this used to be a thick forest
ba.da e.th.w e.re.ra af.y e.th.w en.re.ra we fo.ba nan.fi.yo.kwath
only few ancestors came. the fathers were few. then they made us
fiyoksi = make; bfiyokwre = nakre says this means "we continously make gardens" b= means not so much "there" but more continously. not quite sure what to make of this
we still also make gardens there
gathiksi = leave behind, masu was left fallow for a couple of years
we left the place and waited
b nzf.r.ro a.z.the n bad b.ne b ma.ne e.r.ro
we were there at azthe. we also have some land there
bad tnz.tnz nzen.me b ma.ne e.r.ro b fof nzf.r
we have a small piece of land there. we were there
e fth.m.s zab.the b we kwan.bri.gwre we zn.r ze.na
when we finished the land, we return back again
za.ne y.sa.kwren zf zath.k.fe z.r a.ra.ke thun.bri.gwre ze.na
thkfksi = start, begin; arake thunbrigwre = bringing back the yams
this year we started here. we brought the gardens back now
thkfksi = start, begin; vowel harmony e >
wa.tik tri.ka.si ma.su.a.ne.ma ni.ma zf r b.r
then, this is the story about masu. it is like here this this
ni zf za# kar zf r zf ma.su ma.ne.ma nzr.ko.rth ma.su kar
this place here is masu, that is why they called us masu people
ni ma.su kar zf n.r zf
ywaythk (irreg. no inf) = to come to an end
the story comes to an end there
kaf.md kwot kaf.md f.th ke.ke zf.r.rm
the people used to live in their respective groups
bo.ba wa.zi bm.nzr ni.ma mi.fi.nin a.kri.mo.gon n thwam.nz.rm
msaksi = sit; thwamnzrm = because they don't live there anymore (they moved or they died); thfamnzrm = they lived there for all the time
their lived on the other side like in mibini and in akrimogo others used to live
aw kar ka.ta.ka.tan be.r.ro ni.ma saf.sen be.r
all the small places there in safs over there
msaksi = sit; kwaikr = place near yokwa (where people spoke kancha), daure's wife is from kwaikr

he gathered us to one place
the people went from masu to rouku for good
we made one big village, rouku

when they came with the bibel stories

It brought whatchamacallit ... it brought unity
akonzr = name, become; nakre says this is not "we call each other friends", but "we became friends"
today we are like this here
wa.tik a.ne.ma ni.ma.me fof n.r fof
and that is why we are like this
n.bi ka.re.nzo b b.nam.nzr a.ne.ma za.ne zf

the place where our ancestor settled
msaksi = sit; tried to say: kwamsakwrm (we talked about alternations
where our story man had settled

we left these place and we went there to one village
ma.ne r ni.ma kom.nzo fof r ni.ma

this is really our place here, masu
n m.rn we be.r.ro ni.ma tri.ka.si.ka.r.s fi we ni.m.w e.r.ro
